  <titles>
    <title as="introduced" type="short">Social Security Preservation Act of 1997</title>
    <title as="introduced" type="official">To amend title II of the Social Security Act to ensure the integrity of the social security trust funds by requiring the Managing Trustee to invest the annual surplus of such trust funds in marketable interest-bearing obligations of the United States and certificates of deposit in depository institutions insured by the Federal Deposit Insurance Corporation, and to protect such trust funds from the public debt limit.</title>
